cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the use of periocular region for biometrics, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for detection and segmentation of the region. Hence, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of soft-biometrics, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) techniques, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of databases and algorithms for recognition, which falls under multimedia (MM) and cryptography (CR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the comparison with iris and face modalities, which falls under information retrieval (IR) sub-category.
